---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Experiences - Made the Weekend"
  description="The bookable experiences worth planning a UK weekend around. Tried first; the ones that don't live up to it never make the page."
>
<section class="page-head">
  <div class="inner">
    <svg class="page-motif" width="120" height="44" viewBox="0 0 120 44" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
  <path d="M4 40 C 30 34, 40 22, 60 20 C 74 18.5, 82 17, 89 14" stroke="#E0A45C" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-dasharray="0.5 7" opacity="0.8"></path>
  <path d="M98 2 C 101.3 2, 104 4.7, 104 8 C 104 12.5, 98 17.5, 98 17.5 C 98 17.5, 92 12.5, 92 8 C 92 4.7, 94.7 2, 98 2 Z" stroke="#E0A45C" stroke-width="1.4" fill="none"></path>
  <circle cx="98" cy="7.8" r="1.8" fill="#E0A45C"></circle>
</svg>
    <p class="eyebrow">Experiences</p>
    <h1>The one thing to book before you go</h1>
    <p class="lede">The bookable thing that makes a weekend. We add one only after it's earned its place; if it didn't live up to it, it isn't here.</p>
  </div>
</section>
<section class="dark" style="padding-top:clamp(48px,7vw,72px);padding-bottom:clamp(64px,9vw,100px);">
  <div class="wrap">
    <!--
      ===== EXPERIENCES GO HERE =====
      Add real, tried experiences next session. Keep the same card markup:
      a featured .feat block, then a .grid3 of .g-card items. Each links to a
      real Viator/GetYourGuide affiliate booking, or to the relevant guide.
      Remove the empty-state block below once the first experience is added.
    -->
    <div style="max-width:56ch;">
      <p style="color:var(--sage-light);font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 14px;">
        We're writing these up now. Every experience here will be one we've actually done, booked the way you would, so the first few land alongside the trips they belong to.
      </p>
      <p style="color:var(--sage-light);font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">
        Want to know when they go live? Join <a href="/the-weekend-brief" style="color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">the Weekend Brief</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
</Base>
